Tamil Rebels Plan to Attack Army Camps in North S.Lanka
COLOMBO , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- The Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam ( LTTE ) would be aiming to uproot one of the major army camps in the Mannar area of the Northern Province of Sri Lanka during its " heroes ' week " , according to reports reaching here Sunday .
Military sources were quoted as saying there were reports that a senior LTTE military commander recently was scouting along the banks of the Yoda Weva ( Giant 's Tank ) with a group of rebels .
The sources also said government troops in the region had been alerted and leaves for army soldiers cancelled in view of the rising tension .
The LTTE has threatened to mount all-out attacks on all military camps in the north-east .
But the sources pointed out that the LTTE was finding it difficult to recruit new members into their ranks .
It is believed that the LTTE will be using the " heroes ' week " from November 21 to 27 not only to attack army camps but also launch a concerted recruitment drive .
The LTTE has made arrangements to celebrate the " heroes ' week " and its leader Velupillai Prabhakaran will announce their future political and the military plans on November 26 which is his birthday , according to local press reports .
The government troops in northern Jaffna Peninsula have been alerted not only in the land and the sea but also in skies , the reports added .
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 15-year-old war against the government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island country .
More than 55,000 people have been reportedly killed in the war .
